<subSubSection id="11C46515FFFBFFEEFF0234A734E296E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5961369EFFFBFFEEFF0234A734E296E3" blockId="0.[151,1436,1908,2035]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="6BAAEA8CFFFBFFEEFF0234A7361896C1" bold="true" box="[199,328,1977,2001]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name refers to the centenarian mascot of the Michelin Company, which maintains a private forest reserve in southern Bahia, where the 
<typeStatus id="8665883CFFFBFFEEFDA334C235C496E3" box="[614,660,2012,2035]" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
